cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR 

This paper deals with interference management in device-to-device (D2D) communications underlaying a cellular network, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and wireless communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the path loss model, which is related to information theory and signal processing, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper also analyzes the performance in terms of coverage probability and area spectral efficiency, which are related to multimedia and security, respectively, making cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) possible categories. Finally, the paper addresses the issue of interference management, which is related to cryptography and security, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another possible category.
